Marketing  Media:
   Philadelphia Inquirer
   Reporters Win Award
The education reporting award went to Jeff Gottlieb, at
the San Jose Mercury News, for his coverage of Stanford
University's abuse of government research funds. Mr. Gottlieb
was the first to report that Stanford University had charged
the federal government for flowers, football tickets and
other non-research related expenses.
   The annual George Polk awards for print and broadcast
journalists, selected by Long Island University and
established in 1949, are named for a CBS correspondent
murdered during the Greek civil war.